    American Sign Language:  "brush"
   </span>
  </h2>
  <blockquote>
   <p style="margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0">
    <span style="font-weight: 400">
     Yes, yes, it has been a while since I've used 
one, but it is like riding a bike, once you've learned, you never forget how.
    </span>
    <hr align="left" color="#000000" size="1" width="50%"/>
    <span style="font-weight: 400">
     <p style="margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0">
      The general sign for "brush" is to 
make a couple of brushing movements near your hair, (or in my case, where your 
hair
      <i>
       used
      </i>
      to be).  If you were "brushing a horse" you would spell 
brush and then do couple of brushing movements in the air as if you were 
actually brushing a horse.  If you want to sign "
      <a href="brush-teeth.htm" style="text-decoration: none">
       brush 
your teeth
      </a>
      " you would just make a couple of side to side movements with your 
index finger in front of your teeth.
      <br/>
     </p>
